welcome.name: Welcome
welcome.content:
**INFO**
This is currently a placeholder while I code the acutal wrapper (7/17/2022) ## About A discord selfbot api wrapper heavily based on Discum and Discord.js nothing is private
## Installation **Node.js >= 16.9.0 is required** ```sh-session npm install lunarjs-discord yarn add lunarjs-discord ```

classes.name: Client
classes.description: The main class for interacting with the discord api.

params.name: phone
params.description: Weather or not you want the status to be online via phone

classes.name: BitField
classes.description: Data structure that makes it easy to interact with a bitfield.

props.name: FLAGS
props.description:
Numeric bitfield flags.
<info>Defined in extension classes</info>

methods.name: any
methods.description: Checks whether the bitfield has a bit, or any of multiple bits.

methods.name: equals
methods.description: Checks if this bitfield equals another

methods.name: has
methods.description: Checks whether the bitfield has a bit, or multiple bits.

methods.name: missing
methods.description: Gets all given bits that are missing from the bitfield.

params.name: hasParams
params.description: Additional parameters for the has method, if any

methods.name: freeze
methods.description: Freezes these bits, making them immutable.

returns.description: These bits or new BitField if the instance is frozen.
These bits or new BitField if the instance is frozen.

methods.name: serialize
methods.description:
Gets an object mapping field names to a {@link boolean} indicating whether the
bit is available.

methods.name: toArray
methods.description: Gets an {@link Array} of bitfield names based on the bits available.

methods.name: resolve
methods.description: Resolves bitfields to their numeric form.

typedefs.name: BitFieldResolvable
typedefs.description:
Data that can be resolved to give a bitfield. This can be:
* A bit number (this can be a number literal or a value taken from {@link BitField.FLAGS})
* A string bit number
* An instance of BitField
* An Array of BitFieldResolvable

typedefs.name: WSCodes
typedefs.description:
The types of WebSocket error codes:
* 1000: WS_CLOSE_REQUESTED
* 1011: INTERNAL_ERROR
* 4004: TOKEN_INVALID
* 4010: SHARDING_INVALID
* 4011: SHARDING_REQUIRED
* 4013: INVALID_INTENTS
* 4014: DISALLOWED_INTENTS

typedefs.name: Status
typedefs.description:
The current status of the client. Here are the available statuses:
* READY: 0
* CONNECTING: 1
* RECONNECTING: 2
* IDLE: 3
* NEARLY: 4
* DISCONNECTED: 5
* WAITING_FOR_GUILDS: 6
* IDENTIFYING: 7
* RESUMING: 8

typedefs.name: Endpoints
typedefs.description: An object containing functions that return certain endpoints on the API.

typedefs.name: Opcodes
typedefs.description:
The Opcodes sent to the Gateway:
* DISPATCH: 0
* HEARTBEAT: 1
* IDENTIFY: 2
* STATUS_UPDATE: 3
* VOICE_STATE_UPDATE: 4
* VOICE_GUILD_PING: 5
* RESUME: 6
* RECONNECT: 7
* REQUEST_GUILD_MEMBERS: 8
* INVALID_SESSION: 9
* HELLO: 10
* HEARTBEAT_ACK: 11
* GUILD_SYNC: 12 [Unused]
* DM_UPDATE: 13 #  Send => used to get dm features
* LAZY_REQUEST: 14 #  Send => discord responds back with GUILD_MEMBER_LIST_UPDATE type SYNC...
* LOBBY_CONNECT: 15
* LOBBY_DISCONNECT: 16
* LOBBY_VOICE_STATE_UPDATE: 17 #  Receive
* STREAM_CREATE: 18
* STREAM_DELETE: 19
* STREAM_WATCH: 20
* STREAM_PING: 21 #  Send
* STREAM_SET_PAUSED: 22
* REQUEST_APPLICATION_COMMANDS: 24

The types of events emitted by a Shard:
